        M0["Master Claim"]
        M1["I build production-shaped ML platforms and MLOps systems end to end, from the governed data world they depend on, to the runtime and learning paths they operate through, to the controls, evidence, and operating discipline required to run them under pressure."]
        M2["The fraud platform is the evidence chain that makes that claim believable."]
        M3["A proves the platform is real. Bi proves it earned bounded production readiness. Bii is the current capstone layer where the already-ready platform is taken into live operating responsibility."]
        M0 --> M1 --> M2 --> M3
    end

    subgraph STAGE1["STAGE 1"]
        direction TB
        S1H["1. Solve The World First"]
        S1A["I did not begin with a model, a dashboard, or a thin pipeline. I began by building the world the platform would have to survive."]
        S1B["That meant a layered synthetic fraud data engine that does not just generate fake data, but constructs a governed operating world in stages: merchant geography and demand, routing and civil-time realism, entities, accounts, devices, legitimate behaviour, fraud overlays, labels, and case chronology."]
        S1C["Each stage is validated, each stage has explicit lineage, and downstream components are not allowed to consume outputs unless they have passed legitimacy gates."]
        S1P["<i>Before proving the platform, I engineered the reality the platform would be judged against.</i>"]
        S1H --> S1A --> S1B --> S1C --> S1P
    end

    subgraph STAGE2["STAGE 2"]
        direction TB
        S2H["2. Turn It Into One Shared Operating Reality"]
        S2A["The data engine was not built to feed one experiment. It was built to create one shared, replayable operating world that the whole platform could use."]
        S2B["Runtime replay, stress, supervision, case history, and later ML training and evaluation all draw from the same world instead of from separate toy datasets for separate claims."]
        S2C["The accepted current fraud slice alone carries about 331.5M events, backed by a 473.4M-event raw horizon, with linked label and case surfaces carried alongside it."]
        S2P["<i>I forced the platform, the supervision path, and the ML path to live inside one governed truth path.</i>"]
        S2H --> S2A --> S2B --> S2C --> S2P
    end

    subgraph STAGE3["STAGE 3"]
        direction TB
        S3H["3. Build The System As A Real ML Platform"]
        S3A["On top of that world, I built the platform itself as one production-shaped ML platform rather than a loose stack of tools."]
        S3B["The platform spans ingress and admission, event transport, real-time decisioning, downstream action and outcome handling, case and label operations, governed learning and release, and a governance and meta layer that can reconstruct what happened and defend the claim later."]
        S3C["The learning path runs through managed tooling, Databricks, SageMaker, and MLflow, so runtime, learning, and governance are all part of one operating system instead of separate experiments."]
        S3P["<i>I did not build one pipeline. I built a real platform with owned boundaries and shared controls.</i>"]
        S3H --> S3A --> S3B --> S3C --> S3P
    end

    subgraph STAGE4["STAGE 4"]
        direction TB
        S4H["4. Earn Bounded Production Readiness"]
        S4A["I did not stop at architecture or wiring. I took the platform through bounded production readiness using a proving method that starts plane-first and then re-proves the enlarged coupled platform."]
        S4B["The accepted integrated full-platform proof closed at roughly 3049.811 steady, 6188 burst, and 3019 recovery EPS with clean integrity and downstream timing still intact."]
        S4C["Widened bounded stress authorization then held over 2.36M admitted events at roughly 3007 steady, 6359 burst, and 3017 recovery EPS, while runtime decisions, case and label truth, and governed runtime bundle authority all stayed alive on the same stress story."]
        S4P["<i>I earned the right to say the platform was production-ready on a bounded authorization standard.</i>"]
        S4H --> S4A --> S4B --> S4C --> S4P
    end

    subgraph STAGE5["STAGE 5"]
        direction TB
        S5H["5. Close The Governed MLOps Corridor"]
        S5A["A system like this is not real if runtime and learning are disconnected. So the next layer of the story is that I built the learning corridor as part of the same governed platform, not as a side script."]
        S5B["Runtime, label, and case truth are converted into point-in-time-correct, leakage-safe learning data on managed surfaces. Train and evaluation are governed. Candidate publication is evidence-bearing. Rollback is tested."]
        S5C["Runtime model authority is tied back to governed learning truth instead of drifting away from it."]
        S5P["<i>I owned the path from authoritative world, to bounded dataset basis, to train and evaluation, to governed promotion and rollback, to live runtime authority.</i>"]
        S5H --> S5A --> S5B --> S5C --> S5P
    end

    subgraph STAGE6["STAGE 6"]
        direction TB
        S6H["6. Make It Operable, Challengeable, And Cost-Real"]
        S6A["The system was not declared ready just because it was green. It had to become operable and defendable."]
        S6B["The production standard expects alerting, runbooks, auditable controls, bounded recovery, rollback paths, evidence discipline, and cost realism, so the readiness story made those first-class concerns."]
        S6C["That meant real alert and runbook drills, exact run reconstruction, audit-grade evidence readback, ML day-2 operator surfaces, safe idle and restore controls, and explicit cost-to-outcome discipline."]
        S6D["The operator chain completed through stress backbone, alert drill, ML day-2 surface, operator-ready surface, and stress rollup; the platform could be left safe after the run; and spend was treated as attributable proof cost rather than ambient project spend."]
        S6P["<i>I made the platform something that could be monitored, challenged, recovered, audited, and paid for responsibly.</i>"]
        S6H --> S6A --> S6B --> S6C --> S6D --> S6P
    end

    subgraph STAGE7["STAGE 7"]
        direction TB
        S7H["7. Move Into The Capstone Operating Layer"]
        S7A["Because A and Bi are already earned, the current question is no longer can the platform be built, or can the planes couple. Those questions are already closed."]
        S7B["The Bii layer begins from accepted authority and turns readiness into operating responsibility: live replay, stress windows, incidents and drills, controlled change, audit answerability, operator transferability, learning loops, and cost and evidence closure."]
        S7C["At the same time, the current L4 proving doctrine still defines the stronger long-horizon sustained and endurance standard around a 7-day minimum and 30-day maximum wall-clock window."]
        S7P["<i>The hard threshold has already been crossed; now the work is live operating responsibility.</i>"]
        S7H --> S7A --> S7B --> S7C --> S7P
    end

    subgraph SUMMARY["SUMMARY"]
